- name: note_0
  id: note
  parameters:
    alias: ''
    comment: 'Block B3: Reference Signal Reconstructor


      Demodulates and remodulates the reference signal to create a clean "perfect"
      reference.


      Signal Types:

      - fm: FM Radio (88-108 MHz) - 10-15 dB improvement

      - atsc3: ATSC 3.0 (470-698 MHz) - 15-20 dB improvement

      - dvbt: DVB-T (Europe/Australia)

      - passthrough: No processing (baseline)


      Expected Result:

      Sharper CAF peaks, better detection, fewer false alarms'
    note: BLOCK B3 SETTINGS
  states:
    bus_sink: false
    bus_source: false
    bus_structure: null
    coordinate: [624, 180]
    rotation: 0
    state: enabled

- name: note_1
  id: note
  parameters:
    alias: ''
    comment: 'Signal Flow:


      KrakenSDR (5ch) → AGC → Block B3 (ref only) → ECA → CAF → Doppler → CFAR →
      Cluster → AoA → Tracker


      Block B3 reconstructs the reference channel for 10-20 dB SNR improvement!'
    note: PASSIVE RADAR SIGNAL FLOW
  states:
    bus_sink: false
    bus_source: false
    bus_structure: null
    coordinate: [32, 612]
    rotation: 0
    state: enabled

